books, stamps and coins that it maintains inasmuch as it is not practical to determine a value for such items. Provisions have been made

for appropriate care and security of such collections. No signiﬁcant additions or disposals occurred during the year ended June 30, 2014.

Part III Line 4: The Josephinum was founded in 1888 and is the only Pontiﬁcal College Seminary outside of Italy. It has a rich heritage of

educating seminarians. The collections referred to above enhance the appreciation of Church teaching and culture, especially with the

Pontiﬁcal status and help promote the Josephinum's posture as a historical landmark in Columbus, Ohio. Through its historical

collections and heritage, the Josephinum is able to attract seminarians, faculty, staff and priests to study and work at the Institution.

Part V Line 4: The Josephinum's endowment funds are used for scholarships, ﬁnancial aid, building renovations, instruction, research and

upkeep of the library. All of these areas are in accordance with the mission of the Josephinum in educating seminarians for the priesthood.

Part VI: Lines 153, b: The Budget and Finance Committee of the Board reviews the draft of the Organization's annual budget each year

before it is approved by the full Board of Trustees. In connection with this review, the annual compensation raise for all ofﬁcers, faculty and staff is approved by the Board. The annual raise is equal for all employees. That is, the ofﬁcers of the organization receive the same percentage increase as other employees. The Rector/President executes a contract for his salary that is approved by the Chairman of the Board. In establishing the annual percentage increase in salary for all employees, the Board of Trustees considers the change in the

consumer price index, other religious institution increases and the overall ﬁnancial condition of the Organization to support the increase.
